{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"300b–14","heading":"National contingency plan for newborn screening","label":"300b–14 National contingency plan for newborn screening","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300b–14","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch6A/schIX/ptA","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs300b%E2%80%9314","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2014—Subsec. (a). substituted “consortium” for “consortia” and inserted at end “The plan shall be updated as needed and at least every five years.”Pub. L. 113–240"],"amendments":["Amendments2014—Subsec. (a). substituted “consortium” for “consortia” and inserted at end “The plan shall be updated as needed and at least every five years.”Pub. L. 113–240"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300b–14/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300b–14","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs300b%E2%80%9314%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 180 days after , the Secretary, acting through the Director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and in consultation with the Administrator and State departments of health (or related agencies), shall develop a national contingency plan for newborn screening for use by a State, region, or consortium of States in the event of a public health emergency. The plan shall be updated as needed and at least every five years.April 24, 2008","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Contents","label":"b Contents","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300b–14/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300b–14","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs300b%E2%80%9314%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendm